# Git Hygiene

- Treat the working tree as shared with the user. Never revert, overwrite, or clean up changes you did not make.
- Branch from `hsaab-master` unless the user requests a different base. For upstream syncs, compare against `upstream/master`.
- Before committing, inspect status, diff, and recent log messages. Commit only when explicitly asked.
- Keep commits scoped to the requested work. Do not include unrelated generated files, secrets, build logs, or local config.
- Do not run destructive git commands such as hard reset, force push, or checkout-over-files unless explicitly approved.
- If hooks or formatters modify files, inspect the changes before proceeding.
